				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{OAI}=\left(\mathrm{NT}-\mathrm{NC}\right)/\left(\mathrm{NT}+\mathrm{NC}\right) $$\end{document}OAI=NT−NC/NT+NCwhere NT is the total number of eggs on the treated substrate and NC the total number of eggs on the control substrate (Cheah et al. 2013). For OAI values ≤ −0.3, the EO was considered as repellent (Kramer and Mulla 1979).
